07/08/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Kosovo President Fatmir Sejdiu kicked off a weeklong visit to Albania on Monday (August 6th), meeting with counterpart Bamir Topi. Sejdiu again congratulated Topi on his recent election and briefed him on the challenges Kosovo faces in its bid for independence from Serbia. Topi expressed Albania's readiness to back Kosovo's institutions during the status process. (RFE, 24-ore, Top-Channel, Albanian President Website, RTK, Tanjug - 06/08/07)
